[{"body": "PT Bank Rakyat Indonesia Tbk (BBRI) recorded the highest transaction value in the capital market from January to October 2024, with a share transaction value of IDR 266.26 trillion, accounting for 10.44% of the total transaction value of IDR 2.5 quadrillion. The bank's share price had fallen 22.46% to IDR 4,400 as of the closing transaction price on January 2, 2024, with a trading frequency of 7.76 million times over 198 trading days.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 2, "valuation": 2}, "score": 75, "sector": "financials", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51543/october-transaction-bri-shares-reached-idr", "sub_sector": ["banks"], "tags": ["IDX", "IDX Composite", "Market Trends", "Market Sentiment", "Neutral"], "tickers": ["BBRI.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-11-22T14:20:41", "title": "Bank Rakyat Indonesia records highest transaction value in capital market in 2024."}, {"body": "Foreign investors sold a net 839.82 million shares in the Indonesian market, with major sales in PT GoTo Gojek Tokopedia Tbk (GOTO), PT Bumi Resources Tbk (BUMI), and PT Bank Rakyat Indonesia Tbk (BBRI), among others. Meanwhile, foreign investors purchased a significant number of shares in companies such as PT Buana Lintas Lautan Tbk (BULL), PT Bumi Resources Minerals Tbk (BRMS), and PT Telkom Indonesia Tbk (TLKM), among others.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 0, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 2, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 65, "sector": "technology", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51542/gojek-tokopedia-shares-sold-foreign-volume-falls-shares", "sub_sector": ["software-it-services", "basic-materials", "oil-gas-coal", "banks", "oil-gas-coal", "telecommunication"], "tags": ["Foreign Investor", "IDX", "Market Trends", "Bearish"], "tickers": ["GOTO.JK", "BRMS.JK", "BUMI.JK", "BBRI.JK", "BULL.JK", "TLKM.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-11-22T13:35:38", "title": "Foreign investors sell majority of shares in Indonesian companies, including PT GoTo Gojek Tokopedia and PT Bumi Resources, amidst mixed market activity."}, {"body": "Image Frame Investment Limited, a shareholder of PT MD Entertainment Tbk (FILM), sold 251,667,000 shares or 3% of Film's shares at IDR 1,200 per share, reaping IDR 302 billion in fresh funds, after purchasing the shares at IDR 500 per share in 2021. The sale represents a 140% profit from the purchase price, with the total funds raised amounting to IDR 302 billion, and the shares were sold at a discount of more than 50% compared to the current market price of IDR 3,590 per share.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 2, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 2}, "score": 75, "sector": "consumer-cyclicals", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51541/selling-film-shares-discount-tencent-profit", "sub_sector": ["media-entertainment"], "tags": ["IDX", "Market Trends", "Market Sentiment", "Earnings Report", "Dividends", "Bullish"], "tickers": [], "timestamp": "2024-11-22T13:20:23", "title": "Image Frame Investment sells 3% of Film shares, reaping IDR 302 billion in fresh funds."}, {"body": "Indonesian President Prabowo Subianto secured investment commitments of $8.5 billion from 19 global company leaders at a CEO roundtable forum in London, with potential investors showing interest in the health sector, particularly stem cells. The investment commitments reflect optimism in Indonesia's economy, with CEOs interested in priority sectors such as energy transition, infrastructure, education, and health, and appreciative of the President's policy direction and commitment to clean and efficient government.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 0, "future": 2, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "healthcare", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51540/london-ri-achieved-investment-commitment-us", "sub_sector": ["healthcare-equipment-providers"], "tags": ["Market Trends", "Market Sentiment", "ESG", "Clean Energy", "Foreign Investor", "Bullish"], "tickers": [], "timestamp": "2024-11-22T12:56:04", "title": "Indonesian Government Secures $8.5 Billion Investment Commitment from Global CEOs in London Forum"}, {"body": "PT Honoris Corporindo Pratama (no ticker) increased its stake in PT Modernland Realty Tbk (MDLN) to 29% by acquiring 1.91 billion shares, while PT Panin Sekuritas Tbk (no ticker) facilitated the transaction. Meanwhile, other notable transactions included PT Bogamulia Nagadi (no ticker) increasing its stake in PT Tempo Scan Pacific Tbk (no ticker) to 88.82%, and PT Samuel Tumbuh Bersama (no ticker) reducing its shares in PT Nusantara Sawit Sejahtera Tbk (no ticker) by 50.72 million shares.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 0, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 2, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 65, "sector": "properties-real-estate", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51539/honoris-corporindo-buys-modernland-realty-mdln-shares-increasing-control", "sub_sector": ["properties-real-estate", "investment-service", "pharmaceuticals-health-care-research", "food-beverage"], "tags": ["Mergers & Acquisitions", "Neutral"], "tickers": ["MDLN.JK", "PANS.JK", "TSPC.JK", "NSSS.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-11-22T12:35:00", "title": "Multiple investors and stakeholders make significant changes to their shareholdings in various Indonesian companies."}, {"body": "Foreign investors' net volume closed at -639.87 million shares on Wednesday, November 20, with notable purchases including 57.90 million shares of PT Astrindo Nusantara Infrastruktur Tbk (ASTR) and 36.65 million shares of PT Maharaksa Biru Energi Tbk (MBEN). Meanwhile, significant sales included 2.23 billion shares of PT Goto Gojek Tokopedia Tbk (GOTO), 194.38 million shares of PT Bank Rakyat Indonesia Tbk (BBRI), and 97.39 million shares of PT Telkom Indonesia Tbk (TLKM).", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 0, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 2, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "energy", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51533/foreign-transactions-decrease-foreign-shares", "sub_sector": ["oil-gas-coal", "telecommunication", "software-it-services", "banks", "telecommunication"], "tags": ["Foreign Investor", "IDX", "Neutral"], "tickers": ["BIPI.JK", "OASA.JK", "GOTO.JK", "BBRI.JK", "TLKM.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-11-22T08:40:25", "title": "Foreign investors' net selling reaches 639.87 million shares in Indonesian market on Wednesday."}, {"body": "PT Wijaya Karya Beton Tbk (WTON) has secured new contracts worth IDR 4.99 trillion, or 81% of its 2024 target, with infrastructure projects making up 71.55% of the total and the private sector accounting for 79.26% of the contracts. The company's operating revenue has also increased by 13.64% year-on-year to IDR 3.39 trillion as of September 2024.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 1, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "basic-materials", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51532/wtons-contract-target", "sub_sector": ["basic-materials"], "tags": ["IDX", "Earnings Report", "Market Trends", "Market Sentiment", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["WTON.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-11-21T16:05:57", "title": "Wijaya Karya Beton books new contracts worth IDR 4.99 trillion, reaching 81% of 2024 target."}, {"body": "PT Bank Maybank Indonesia Tbk (BNII) will auction off PT Dafam Mambo International's land and building in Semarang, Central Java, worth IDR 72.71 billion, after negotiation efforts fell through. The remaining proceeds from the auction, after settling the bank debt, will be used to boost PT Dafam Property Indonesia Tbk's (DMAM) capital, following a credit restructuring agreement that included a grace period and deferred interest payments.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 65, "sector": "financials", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51531/negotiation-fails-maybank-auction-dfams-land", "sub_sector": ["banks", "consumer-services"], "tags": ["Debt", "Bonds", "Market Trends", "IDX", "Neutral"], "tickers": ["BNII.JK", "DFAM.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-11-21T15:55:56", "title": "Maybank Indonesia to Auction Dafam Mambo International's Land and Building in Semarang Worth IDR 72.71 Billion"}, {"body": "PT BFI Finance Tbk (BFIN) aims to achieve 5% year-on-year growth in assets financing by the end of 2024, targeting assets of Rp25.2 trillion, and new financing distribution of Rp20 trillion. In Q3 2024, BFIN posted quarter-on-quarter improvements, with new financing growing 19.1%, revenue increasing 2.7%, and net profit rising 32.3%, despite a decline in new financing and revenue in September 2024 due to the sluggish automotive market.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 2, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "financials", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51530/automotive-market-slumps-bfi-finance-sets-growth-target-year-end", "sub_sector": ["financing-service", "food-beverage", "oil-gas-coal", "retailing", "heavy-constructions-civil-engineering", "heavy-constructions-civil-engineering", "financing-service", "oil-gas-coal", "oil-gas-coal", "basic-materials", "banks", "banks", "food-beverage", "oil-gas-coal", "insurance", "banks", "industrial-goods", "basic-materials", "investment-service", "food-staples-retailing", "food-beverage", "basic-materials", "holding-investment-companies", "properties-real-estate", "basic-materials", "utilities", "properties-real-es