growth target for 2024 amid sluggish automotive market."}, {"body": "PT Jakarta Setiabudi Internasional Tbk (JSPT) will develop a residential condominium in Sanur, Bali, by 2025, with a capital expenditure budget of IDR 400-500 billion, driven by rising demand for residential properties in Bali over the past 2-3 years. The company will allocate its capital expenditure budget to three projects: the Sanur residential project, revitalizing Bali Collection near Nusa Dua, and sustainability development at Puri Botanical Resident in Sumatera.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 1, "future": 2, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 1, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "consumer-cyclicals", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51529/jspt-residential-project-sanur", "sub_sector": ["consumer-services"], "tags": ["IDX", "Market Trends", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["JSPT.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-11-21T15:09:21", "title": "PT Jakarta Setiabudi Internasional to Develop Residential Condominium in Sanur, Bali by 2025"}, {"body": "PT Citra Tubindo Tbk (CTBN) reported a net profit of USD 18.46 million in the first nine months of 2024, a 59% year-on-year increase from USD 11.6 million in the same period last year, driven by solid revenue growth of 13% to USD 168.66 million. The company aims to reach revenue of USD 291.44 million and net profit of USD 19.69 million in 2024, with export sales services remaining a key contributor, and plans to strengthen its export market user portfolio following its expansion success in the Middle East and Africa.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 2, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "basic-materials", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51523/profit-soaring-m-citra-tubindo-grows-optimistic", "sub_sector": ["basic-materials"], "tags": ["Earnings Report", "IDX", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["CTBN.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-11-21T10:45:44", "title": "PT Citra Tubindo Tbk Sees 59% Increase in Net Profit to USD 18.46 Million in First Nine Months of 2024"}, {"body": "PT Dian Swastatika Sentosa Tbk (DSSA) is issuing a shelf-registration bond Sukuk Mudharabah I Phase III worth IDR 3.5 trillion, with proceeds allocated to pay off bank loans (41.7%) and fund various business activities, including a loan to PT SMLPlus Sentra Data (19.1%) and expansion of its internet service provider (17.1%). The bond will be issued in three series, with yields ranging from 6.5% to 8.625% per annum, and tenors of 370 days to 5 years.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "energy", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51522/paying-bank-loans-dssa-issue-bond-sukuk-idr", "sub_sector": ["oil-gas-coal"], "tags": ["Bonds", "Debt", "IDX", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["DSSA.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-11-21T09:34:28", "title": "PT Dian Swastatika Sentosa to Issue IDR 3.5 Trillion Sukuk Mudharabah Bond to Repay Bank Loans and Fund Business Expansion"}, {"body": "PT Chemstar Indonesia Tbk (CHEM) aims to reach IDR 207 billion in revenue by 2025, driven by growth in its energy and agrobusiness segments, with revenue targets of IDR 60 billion and IDR 20 billion, respectively. The company expects 10%, 50%, and 300% growth in its textile, energy, and agrobusiness segments, respectively, with the textile segment contributing 60% of total revenue and energy-agrobusiness covering the remaining 40%.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 2, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "basic-materials", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51521/chem-aims-idr-revenue", "sub_sector": ["basic-materials"], "tags": ["Energy Commodities", "Earnings Report", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["CHEM.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-11-20T17:44:11", "title": "PT Chemstar Indonesia targets IDR 207 billion revenue in 2025 driven by growth in energy and agrobusiness segments."}, {"body": "Bank Indonesia maintained its benchmark interest rate at 6.00% to control inflation, targeted at 2.5% for 2024 and 2025, amidst escalating global economic uncertainties. The rupiah has depreciated 0.84% due to the broad-based strengthening of the US dollar, driven by the US government's fiscal policies and global investors reallocating portfolios back to US assets.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 0, "future": 1, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "financials", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51520/bank-indonesia-rate-weakness", "sub_sector": ["banks", "banks", "banks", "banks"], "tags": ["Interest Rates", "Inflation", "IDX", "Bearish"], "tickers": ["BBHI.JK", "BNII.JK", "BBSI.JK", "MCOR.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-11-20T16:55:40", "title": "Bank Indonesia Maintains Benchmark Interest Rate at 6% to Control Inflation and Stabilize Rupiah Amid Global Economic Uncertainties."}]